                <h4>What is the voting age population of Marissa, Illinois?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Marissa, Illinois, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 1,160.  The voting age population is 49.7% male and 50.3% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Marissa, Illinois residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 28.9% of
                        the residents of Marissa are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Marissa, Illinois?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Marissa are 99.5% White, 0.3% Black and 0.2% Two or more races.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Marissa, Illinois residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Marissa, 15.5% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 19.1%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    11.2% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Marissa.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Marissa, Illinois residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 54.3% of
                    Marissa residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Marissa, Illinois residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    89.6% of
                    Marissa residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 11.0%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 5.4%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Marissa, Illinois residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Marissa residents aged 5 and older, 2.9% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                0.4% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.1% speak an Indo-European language, and
                1.4% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Marissa, Illinois?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Marissa is 6.6%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Marissa, Illinois residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Marissa, 4.7% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Marissa, Illinois?</h4>
